                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On February 7, 1950, the Department of State announced that the United States had
                    accorded diplomatic recognition to the Governments of the State of Viet-Nam, the
                    Kingdom of Laos, and the Kingdom of Cambodia. For the text of the Department’s
                    press release, see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, February
                    20, 1950, pages 291–292.</p>
                <p>The United Kingdom also recognized the three Governments on February 7. For the
                    text of the note delivered by Sir Oliver Harvey, British Ambassador in Paris, to
                    the French Ministry of Foreign Affairs, see Great Britain, Parliament, <hi
                        rend="italic">Documents Relating to British Involvement in the Indo-China
                        Conflict, 1945–1965</hi>, Cmnd. 2834 (London: Her Majesty’s Stationery
                    Office, 1965), page 56.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
